The influence of all other factors on the supply is manifested in the movement of the supply curve.

01:12:35.000 --> 01:12:43.000
Right-down when the supply increases and left-up when it decreases.

01:12:44.000 --> 01:12:45.000
Let's try to figure it out.

01:12:45.000 --> 01:12:49.000
What does it mean that the supply has increased?

01:12:50.000 --> 01:13:03.000
It means that at the same price, they want to offer more goods than before.

01:13:04.000 --> 01:13:11.000
Let's say, before, at the price of $10 per barrel, how much was offered for sale?

01:13:12.000 --> 01:13:13.000
2 barrels of oil.

