To give the right answer, you need to stand on the position of the farmer-producer.

01:19:10.000 --> 01:19:11.000
In no case on the position of the consumer.

01:19:12.000 --> 01:19:13.000
We won't understand anything like that.

01:19:14.000 --> 01:19:15.000
It is the position of the farmer.

01:19:17.000 --> 01:19:19.000
What do farmers focus on?

01:19:21.000 --> 01:19:23.000
On the profitability of one or another product.

01:19:25.000 --> 01:19:27.000
The carrot is more expensive.

01:19:28.000 --> 01:19:33.000
So the profitability of the carrot for the farmers has increased under other equal conditions.

01:19:34.000 --> 01:19:35.000
What do the farmers answer?

01:19:37.000 --> 01:19:40.000
They increase the offer of the carrot.

01:19:41.000 --> 01:19:44.000
And in fact, look at the slide.

01:19:45.000 --> 01:19:48.000
Previously, the carrot cost P1.

01:19:49.000 --> 01:19:51.000
The market offered Q1 carrots.

01:19:52.000 --> 01:19:54.000
Now the carrot costs P2.

01:19:54.000 --> 01:19:58.000
And the market offers Q2 carrots.

01:19:59.000 --> 01:20:03.000
So with the price increase, the farmers increase the offer of the carrot.

