01:28:32.000 --> 01:28:33.000
This is how it is done on the slide.

01:28:35.000 --> 01:28:37.000
Two curves of demand and supply.

01:28:38.000 --> 01:28:39.000
Let's discuss.

01:28:40.000 --> 01:28:50.000
Let's assume that at the beginning the price was at the level of P1.

01:28:51.000 --> 01:28:52.000
P1.

01:28:53.000 --> 01:28:55.000
Look, what are we going to observe?

01:28:56.000 --> 01:28:58.000
You see, the price is high.

01:28:59.000 --> 01:29:06.000
At this price, the demand will be small.

01:29:07.000 --> 01:29:08.000
What is it equal to on the graph?

01:29:09.000 --> 01:29:10.000
Q1d.

01:29:11.000 --> 01:29:12.000
You see?

01:29:13.000 --> 01:29:19.000
At the price of P1, the demand is Q1d.

01:29:21.000 --> 01:29:25.000
At such a high price, few people would want to buy this product.

01:29:26.000 --> 01:29:28.000
And what do you say about the offer?

