01:29:57.000 --> 01:30:00.000
And on the market, we observe the commodity.

01:30:01.000 --> 01:30:09.000
Manufacturers want to sell more goods than the consumers agree to buy at such a price.

01:30:12.000 --> 01:30:20.000
I must say that in this model we are looking at the so-called completely competitive market.

01:30:21.000 --> 01:30:24.000
What is a completely competitive market?

01:30:24.000 --> 01:30:30.000
It is a market in which there are a lot of independent sellers and buyers.

01:30:31.000 --> 01:30:35.000
No one separately controls the price.

01:30:36.000 --> 01:30:44.000
The price on the market is set spontaneously, under the influence of the demand of thousands of buyers and the offer of hundreds of sellers.

01:30:45.000 --> 01:30:55.000
But still, at the price of P1, when sellers cannot sell their goods, the price spontaneously begins to decrease.

01:30:58.000 --> 01:31:08.000
Let's see now what happens if the price on the market is accidentally set to the level of P2.

01:31:09.000 --> 01:31:12.000
What do we observe at the price of P2?

01:31:15.000 --> 01:31:17.000
The price is low.

01:31:18.000 --> 01:31:23.000
At such a price, many would be happy to buy this product.

01:31:24.000 --> 01:31:30.000
And the demand value for the product is, look at the slide, Q2d.

01:31:31.000 --> 01:31:33.000
But the price is low for manufacturers.

01:31:34.000 --> 01:31:41.000
At such a price, very few manufacturers would like to produce and sell this product.

01:31:41.000 --> 01:31:45.000
That is, at the price of P2, the product will be offered to the market.

01:31:46.000 --> 01:31:47.000
Q2s.

01:31:48.000 --> 01:31:50.000
What do we observe now?

01:31:51.000 --> 01:31:57.000
They want to sell, they want to buy more goods than they want to sell.

01:31:58.000 --> 01:32:00.000
What is the difference called?

01:32:01.000 --> 01:32:02.000
Do you know this word?

01:32:03.000 --> 01:32:05.000
Of course, it is a deficit.

01:32:06.000 --> 01:32:08.000
A deficit arises on the market.

01:32:08.000 --> 01:32:12.000
And the price of the product starts to rise.

01:32:14.000 --> 01:32:17.000
And the next step, what do we observe?

01:32:18.000 --> 01:32:20.000
Look carefully at the slide.

01:32:22.000 --> 01:32:32.000
There is some price, P with an asterisk, at which the quantities of demand and supply coincide with each other.

01:32:33.000 --> 01:32:40.000
